One expensive activity that I really enjoy doing occasionally is travelling. Whenever I feel stressed from the hectic face of city life, I like to take short trips to explore new destinations. Travelling allows me to refresh my mind, experience different cultures, and broaden my perspective on life.
I usually travel alone because I enjoy the sense of independence and freedom it gives me. Before each trip, I spend time researching the destination online, learning about its main attractions, local cuisine, and the friendliness of the people. Feeling welcomed by locals is very important to me.
Travelling can be quite expensive due to transporation, accommodation, and food costs. To manage my budget, I often say in hostels instead of hotels.
Even though it requires careful preparation, I absolutely love travelling because it gives me a strong sense of autonomy and provides many unique and memorable experiences.

