When it comes to an expensive activity that I truly enjoy from time to time, travelling would be at the top of my list. Because I love a rather fast-paced urban lifestyle, I occasionally feel overwhelmed by the hustle and bustle of city life, so travelling gives me a perfect opportunity to escape my routine and recharge mentally.

Most of the time, I prefer travellling alone because it gives me a strong sense of independence and complete flexibility in planning my itinerary, Solo trips allow me to explore destinations at my own pace and step outside my comfort zone, which makes the experience even more rewarding.

Travelling can be quite costly for several reasons. Transporation expenses, accommodation, food and entrance fees to popular attractions can quickly add up. Even though I try to reduce costs by choosing budget accommodation like hostels and planning carefully, it still requires a significant financial commitment.

Before each trip, I usually do through research online about the destination, including must-see landmarks, local cuisine, and especially the friendliness and hospitality of the locals, since I feel more comfortable visting places where visitors are warmly welcomed. I also make sure to pack all the essential items such as identification documents, insurance, and basic medical supplies to ensure a smooth journey.

Overall, travelling makes me feel incrediblity fulfilled. It allows me to immerse myself in different cultures, broaden my horizons, and gain fresh perspectives on life. Despite the expense, the memorable experiences and personal growth I gain made it absolutely worthwhile.
